The paper discusses the possible causes of non-citation in academic research, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the importance of citations in academic research, which is closely related to digital libraries. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses the factors that influence the citation of research papers, which is a topic that falls under information retrieval. cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is another possible category as the paper discusses the importance of the title of a research paper, which is closely related to natural language processing. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also possible as the paper discusses the quality of content and the importance of self-citation, which are topics that fall under cryptography and security. Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also possible as the paper discusses the academic tastes and interests of researchers, which is a topic that falls under social and information networks.
